ActOther Than Statutory Authority
PrecisAppointment of AILISH JOHNSON CAMPBELL to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the European Union, in Brussels; NATASHA CAYER to be Ambassador and Permanent Delegate of Canada to the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, in Paris; ANNICK GOULET to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of Moldova, with residence in Bucharest; JENNY HILL to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Republic of South Sudan; JOCELYN KINNEAR to be Ambassador and Permanent Representative of Canada to the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe, in Vienna; and REID SIRRS to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of Canada to the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan.
